Website Live - https://fresh-save3.vercel.app/

✅ Real-World Problem (Ground Reality)
Small grocery stores, kirana shops, and local vendors lose 10–20% of perishable inventory daily due to:

No tracking of product freshness Manual guesswork in pricing No real-time visibility of spoilage Lack of automation tools (unlike big chains)

👉 In places like local markets across Delhi or tier-2 cities, shopkeepers rely on experience, not data.

💥 Result:

Fruits/vegetables rot on shelves Late discounts = no buyers Direct profit loss 2. 🎯 Problem Statement (Hackathon-Ready)

“How can small and medium grocery retailers reduce perishable inventory loss by dynamically adjusting pricing based on real-time product freshness, without requiring expensive infrastructure or complex AI systems?”

🚀 Solution (Refined + Strong Pitch) 💡 Solution Name:
Retail-Drain: AI-Powered Dynamic Discounting System

🔧 How It Works (Clear & Practical) 🧠 Agent 1 – Inventory Awareness Tracks when items were stocked Uses simple rules (e.g., “banana > 3 days = risk zone”) 👁️ Agent 2 – Visual Intelligence Camera scans shelves Uses YOLOv8 to detect: Browning bananas 🍌 Wilted spinach 🥬 Overripe fruits

👉 Instead of predicting demand, it detects actual physical decay

💸 Agent 3 – Smart Pricing Engine Adjusts price dynamically: Fresh → Full price Slightly spoiled → 10–20% off Near expiry → 30–50% off Updates via: QR code labels Digital price display 🔁 Workflow Summary

Shelf → Camera → Spoilage Detection → Pricing Logic → Discount Applied → Faster Sales
